NUMBER 645
NAME Tower, Dome
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Here at the top of the crystal tower you find yourself in a room
alive with energy, sights, and sounds. The rough surface of the
dome-shaped ceiling arches some fifty feet above you and has what
seems like thousands of crystalline facets of all colors, shapes,
and sizes. Each facet pulses with its own unique hue and tone.
The mirror-bright floor shines with the dancing reflections. In the
center of the room is a crystal pedestal that emits a radiant
white light, seemingly the focal point of the luminous music of the
facets overhead. As the light and sound fill your senses, you
can feel it drawing you near with an irresistible power that tugs at
your most inner being. You have a strange urge to touch the pedestal.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT D 482
ITEM 0  292 ADJ1=37 ADJ2=145

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
As you look upon the pedestal you become aware of what it truly is.
It is not only the focus for all the lights and sounds of this tower,
but also of the magic, life, and soul of this place: it is sentient.
*DESCRIPTION_END

  IFPREVERB TOUCH 0
    CLEARVERB
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 30
    ECHO PLAYER A voice says,"Now you sense it, now you know....."
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER A voice says,"I am the Crystal Tower."
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER A voice says,"Before you enter the world of Andor, you must be made aware of two things."
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER  A voice says,"The first is a warning: we are a rather unique race here. And because of that some do not trust us. You may never encounter this mistrust, and I hope you do not. But told of it you had to be."
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER A voice says,"The second thing is a part of our past here. There was a time of war. Our kind was not suited for such things. There were some who learned the ways of making mechanical bodies, machines of war."
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER A voice says,"Some of our people entered these creations and became one with them, never again to live free without form as we do."
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER A voice says,"In time the war ended, and the need for these creations ended. But sadly, to this day some of our people are brought into being as these creations. They are called the Mechanoids."
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER A voice says,"I hope I have prepared you well. Step into the pedestal, and enter the world of Andor."
    IFVAR INTNUM6 = 8
      EQUAL INTNUM6 9
    ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 0
  IFVAR INTNUM6 > 8
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO OTHERS %N walks into the pedestal.
    ECHO PLAYER You walk directly into the pedestal and become bathed in warmth. After a brief disorientation you find yourself standing before the gates of a great city.
    ; FInal counter, must be 10 by time you get to Fayd.
    IFVAR INTNUM6 = 9
      EQUAL INTNUM6 10
    ENDIF
    PLREVENT 1
    CONTPLREVENT
    MOVE 501
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER Please touch the pedestal to absorb its wisdom.
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB DOWN -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO OTHERS %N sinks into the floor.
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER You merge with floor and enter the room below.
  SHOWROOM 482
  AFFECT 482
  ECHO OTHERS %N form out of the floor.
  AFFECT 645
  MOVE 482
ENDIF
